      <mRID>90811646-1e71-451e-aa87-594010a8fe70</mRID>
      <name>Manage flexibility activations</name>
      <Narrative>
        <completeDescription />
        <mRID>04355ac9-0c6c-4650-bbab-3783859fb810</mRID>
        <shortDescription>Description of the needed data exchange for the selection (taking into account any grid limitations) and initiation of activation of flexibilities bids that previously have been sent to the Flexibility Platform. Delivery of notification of activation requests to the Flexibility Service Providers (FSPs), in a reliable and timely manner according to the relevant terms and conditions applicable to FSPs.&lt;br/&gt;According to EU-SysFlex WP3 suggestion, the function of grid impact assessment and hosting of Grid Validation System could be taken over by Optimisation Operator role from the Primary and Secondary System Operator roles.</shortDescription>
      </Narrative>
      <nature>SUC</nature>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description />
        <mRID>3fc8c3c0-05b1-402b-ae36-7351b6c58f1f</mRID>
        <name>FSPs have been prequalified and have submitted bids.</name>
        <number>1</number>
      </Prerequisite>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description>TSOs and DSOs request and initiate activation of flexibilities for their own needs regardless in whose network the flexibility is located. The validation of the flexibility initiation is always done by the SO where the flexibility is connected and whose grid is impacted. Flexibilities can be activated in real time (e.g. FCR) or not (e.g. FRR).</description>
        <mRID>daeecbfe-7ce6-4c1c-aaf7-c9e30227cdcf</mRID>
        <name>TSOs and DSOs play equivalent roles in this use case</name>
        <number>2</number>
      </Prerequisite>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description />
        <mRID>fc7dab67-b77e-4b9d-9f9d-d2d87ce62058</mRID>
        <name>FSPs are being selected by the PSO based on bids in merit order list taking  into account the sensitivities and limitations he receives from the SO.</name>
        <number>3</number>
      </Prerequisite>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description />
        <mRID>207f72e6-d5cf-4265-8ce3-0ff629375ba8</mRID>
        <name>Flexibility activation should not create congestion in any grid.</name>
        <number>4</number>
      </Prerequisite>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description />
        <mRID>ec881471-155d-4629-9845-bafa07cacd1e</mRID>
        <name>Flexibility Service Providers and System Operators need their own applications to connect to the Flexibility Platform.</name>
        <number>5</number>
      </Prerequisite>
      <Prerequisite>
        <description />
        <mRID>310de35f-33c0-4511-88be-7e5851a99373</mRID>
